<HL>
   Thomson-CSF S.A.
   Gets 3 Airport Orders
   ----
   Special to The Wall Street Journal
</HL>
<DATE>
09/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   TCSFY EUROP
</CO>
<IN>
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<LP>
   PARIS -- Thomson-CSF S.A. said it received three civil
aviation contracts, all for undisclosed amounts.
   France's state-controlled defense and electronics group
said it received an order for a voice communications control
system for Britain's Civil Aviation Authority. The new
equipment will be used to handle communications at Manchester
Airport.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Thomson-CSF also announced a contract for a terminal
control radar system for Denmark's Aarhus-Tirstrup airport,
to be operational by mid-1991.
   Also, the company said it won an order from Belgium's
national air control system for an autonomous monopulse
secondary radar to be used at Brussels National Airport. The
order also includes an upgrading of a station in Saint
Hubert. The new equipment is scheduled to come into service
at the end of 1991.
</TEXT>
